oc:kn_20b906ad a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During Phase 4 validation of populated slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow the validate-fix-repeat loop with a maximum of 3 cycles. After 3 cycles, document remaining issues and escalate to user with an explicit disclaimer." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Some issues (font rendering, complex shape alignment) require manual PowerPoint intervention and cannot be fixed programmatically." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7272d5a8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any template population" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always create a backup of the original template ([filename]_backup.pptx) before any modifications. Direct XML editing or unexpected errors can corrupt files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "PowerPoint XML editing carries corruption risk. A backup enables recovery without re-downloading the template." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_865c52dc a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting financial figures for presentation slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Rounding conventions: Large market sizes ($10bn+) → nearest $1bn; CAGR → whole % or 0.5%; Multiples → 1 decimal; Market share → nearest 5%. Rounding should not materially change the figure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent rounding prevents reader confusion and maintains credibility while keeping figures readable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_984e8965 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When soffice conversion fails during validation phase" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If PDF/image conversion fails: check LibreOffice installed (which soffice), try libreoffice --headless alternative, or open manually in PowerPoint/LibreOffice and export." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Validation cannot proceed without visual output. These fallback steps avoid blocking the entire workflow." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a4a621c7 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting parallel content sections on slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Same-level boxes must use identical font sizes. Vertically stacked boxes must have identical left margin, bullet indentation, text start position, and width. Horizontally adjacent boxes must have identical top position and height." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Inconsistent formatting across parallel elements signals careless work and undermines professional credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b2677f59 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using LibreOffice for visual validation (soffice --headless --convert-to pdf)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "LibreOffice does NOT render PowerPoint files accurately — it mangles fonts, gradients, shape positions, and text wrapping. Always include the LibreOffice disclaimer when delivering output." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Validation catches structural issues but cannot catch font substitution, alignment shifts, or gradient problems that only appear in Microsoft PowerPoint." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c6f8062b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When populating body content areas that had placeholder formatting" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never inherit placeholder contrast schemes (light text on colored backgrounds) for production body content. Apply dark text (#000000 or #333333) on white/light backgrounds instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Placeholder colors are deliberately distinct to signal 'replace me.' Inheriting them produces hard-to-read output." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d1891c9f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing template structure before population" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Distinguish between two placeholder types: Instruction boxes (bright colors, guidance text → DELETE entire shape) vs Layout placeholders (neutral colors, part of slide master → KEEP shape, replace text only)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Deleting layout placeholders breaks template structure, while keeping instruction boxes produces unprofessional output." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_d3066a3c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When adding footnotes and source citations to slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every superscript number (¹²³) in slide body MUST have a corresponding Notes entry in the footnote format: 'Sources: [Source] (Year). Notes: (1) [Note].'" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unresolved superscript references are a common audit finding and undermine the deck's credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d5562998 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When encountering colored instruction boxes (yellow, orange) with guidance text in templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never populate data INTO placeholder instruction boxes while keeping their colored formatting. Delete the entire instruction shape and create new content with production formatting (dark text on light background)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Instruction boxes tell you WHAT to create, not HOW to format it. Keeping placeholder formatting results in unprofessional slides with wrong contrast." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_df0531ee a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, at the very beginning of any pitch deck task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Read ALL reference files (formatting-standards.md, slide-templates.md, xml-reference.md, calculation-standards.md) at task start before beginning any work." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reference files contain critical patterns and anti-patterns that affect approach. Discovering them late causes rework." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e6293147 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before delivering the populated template (Phase 5)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify: all figures match sources, no [bracket] placeholders remain, tables are actual objects, text readable against backgrounds, cross-slide figures identical, logo present, no placeholder boxes retained." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The final quality checklist catches data errors, formatting issues, and template compliance problems before delivery." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ed98622a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any tabular data on slides" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create tables using pipe characters (|), tabs, or space-separated text. Tables MUST be actual PowerPoint table objects created via python-pptx or proper OOXML." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Text-based 'tables' never align properly, cannot be formatted consistently, and look unprofessional. They are not editable by recipients." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_fe3513f9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When programmatically editing PowerPoint files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use python-pptx for creating new tables, adding text boxes, inserting images, and most shape creation. Use direct XML editing ONLY for modifying properties python-pptx doesn't expose. NEVER use direct XML for creating tables from scratch." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Direct XML table creation has relationship management issues that can corrupt the file. python-pptx handles this safely." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

